#circuitbreakersg day 27

Made some scotch eggs with chorizo for brunch today with a side of rocket and baby spinach, cherry tomatoes, nuts and smoked salmon. 🥚 🌭 🌱🍅 🥜 🐠 .
.
.
If circuit breaker was not extended, tomorrow would have been the last day. So let’s give ourselves a pat on our shoulders for coming this far! 👍🏻 .
.
.
Since circuit breaker started, I have been cooking a lot more than before and the hubs always helps to clean up after our meals. This is what I’m grateful for today. 😊 #gratitudediary
.
.
.

The scotch egg looks so tempting😋

@lovedbyro I brought the water to a boil, lowered it to a simmer and put the eggs inside and covered the pot, left it to simmer for about 4 mins, off the fire, and left the lid on for another 2 mins. And took out the eggs and put in a cold bath. 😃
I need to learn cooking this egg also 🌈
Egg looks amazing !! Cooked to perfection !
